for SerDe of the maps, I would recommend using:
    Map<String, String> pairs = Splitter.on(",").withKeyValueSeparator(":").split(serialized);
    state =  pairs.entrySet().stream()
        .collect(Collectors.toMap(
            e -> KafkaStreams.State.valueOf(e.getKey()),
            e -> Integer.parseInt(e.getValue()),
            (v1, v2) -> {throw new IllegalStateException("duplicate keys")},
            TreeMap::new
        ));
And you can use the correspond method to serialize: Joiner.on(",").withKeyValueSeparator(":").join(values);

